1
00:00:01,602 --> 00:00:02,572
   

2
00:00:02,572 --> 00:00:08,103
Do Jun told me to drop you off safe and sound.

3
00:00:08,850 --> 00:00:14,930


4
00:00:14,930 --> 00:00:15,830
   

5
00:00:15,830 --> 00:00:17,282
When you get there,

6
00:00:17,282 --> 00:00:21,353
you'll see Do Jun's employees from Miracle waiting for you.

7
00:00:22,053 --> 00:00:26,223
I guess you'll be away for quite a while.

8
00:00:27,323 --> 00:00:30,992
No one at Jeongsimjae seemed to know about it.

9
00:00:30,992 --> 00:00:33,763
Why didn't you tell them?

10
00:00:35,463 --> 00:00:40,273
Do Jun told me everything.

11
00:00:45,073 --> 00:00:47,083
Mother, I have to say,

12
00:00:47,713 --> 00:00:49,613
you are a scary person.

13
00:00:51,582 --> 00:00:57,282
Your Soonyang Insurance shares, I heard you handed them over to Do Jun.

14
00:00:59,592 --> 00:01:04,192
From the day my birth mother brought me to Jeongsimjae to this very moment,

15
00:01:04,192 --> 00:01:05,993
I have always

16
00:01:07,103 --> 00:01:12,133
felt uncomfortable around you and found you inaccessible.

17
00:01:12,133 --> 00:01:13,903
You see,

18
00:01:15,442 --> 00:01:18,642
I've done my very best to take good care of you.

19
00:01:19,713 --> 00:01:21,983
I treated you just like I treated my own children.

20
00:01:21,983 --> 00:01:26,152
I always bought you nice clothes and fed you good food.

21
00:01:26,152 --> 00:01:29,352
But with your eyes, you always told me this.

22
00:01:29,352 --> 00:01:33,292
"If you have a conscience, you should not forget my kindness."

23
00:01:33,292 --> 00:01:37,932
"So don't you dare dream of succeeding the throne at Soonyang."

24
00:01:38,792 --> 00:01:40,862
All my life,

25
00:01:41,633 --> 00:01:45,133
I've lived as if I was protesting against you, Mother.

26
00:01:46,472 --> 00:01:50,242
Going against Father's wishes and studying films.

27
00:01:50,242 --> 00:01:54,743
Marrying someone you and Father disapproved of. All of it.

28
00:01:56,013 --> 00:01:57,853
But it turns out,

29
00:02:00,053 --> 00:02:02,583
I'm even worse than you.

30
00:02:04,222 --> 00:02:08,962
The cruel bunch who can do anything for their children.

31
00:02:10,662 --> 00:02:14,262
I suppose all parents are like that after all, Mother.

32
00:02:16,173 --> 00:02:19,333
Now that I've become one of such parents,

33
00:02:20,542 --> 00:02:23,373
I can finally understand

34
00:02:25,542 --> 00:02:29,912
how hurt you must've been by my existence

35
00:02:31,252 --> 00:02:35,123
in and of itself, every single moment.

36
00:02:39,252 --> 00:02:44,322
Mother, I respect you for enduring it all through these years.

37
00:03:15,023 --> 00:03:15,924
   

38
00:03:15,924 --> 00:03:17,692
Regarding Lee Pil Ok's borrowed-name account,

39
00:03:17,692 --> 00:03:21,162
we found out that there was a large transaction recently.

40
00:03:21,162 --> 00:03:24,572
The Soonyang Insurance shares she had purchased...

41
00:03:24,572 --> 00:03:25,873
   

42
00:03:25,873 --> 00:03:29,603
Here. She's transferred them to Jin Do Jun.

43
00:03:29,603 --> 00:03:33,082
   
   

44
00:03:35,743 --> 00:03:37,212
Ma'am.

45
00:03:37,212 --> 00:03:39,183
Lee Pil Ok isn't in the country.

46
00:03:39,183 --> 00:03:41,683
- What? 
 - She already left the country.

47
00:03:41,683 --> 00:03:44,533
I confirmed it with Immigration just now.

48
00:03:45,670 --> 00:03:48,080
   
   

49
00:03:51,793 --> 00:03:53,602
   

50
00:04:02,072 --> 00:04:03,772
It was you, wasn't it?

51
00:04:05,642 --> 00:04:08,012
Your grandmother.

52
00:04:08,012 --> 00:04:10,612
Lee Pil Ok, the prime suspect in the proxy murder case.

53
00:04:10,612 --> 00:04:12,812
You helped her flee the country.

54
00:04:16,152 --> 00:04:18,252
Did you cut a deal with her?

55
00:04:18,952 --> 00:04:21,702
Because of her Soonyang Insurance shares?

56
00:04:25,832 --> 00:04:31,562
I tried so hard to catch her, yet you cut a deal with her.

57
00:04:31,562 --> 00:04:34,073
You, of all people,

58
00:04:34,073 --> 00:04:36,723
know why I wanted to catch her so much.

59
00:04:38,173 --> 00:04:40,523
You've got nothing to say, right?

60
00:04:46,683 --> 00:04:49,382
Just this once. We're almost there, Min Yeong.

61
00:04:49,382 --> 00:04:51,322
It'll all be over once I'm appointed CEO at the shareholders' meeting.

62
00:04:51,322 --> 00:04:53,963
I won't let you down anymore.

63
00:04:55,623 --> 00:04:57,232
You're wrong.

64
00:04:58,332 --> 00:05:00,782
You'll become even more dishonorable.

65
00:05:02,402 --> 00:05:05,152
Because you'll want to keep your position.

66
00:05:31,632 --> 00:05:33,132
Honey,

67
00:05:33,933 --> 00:05:38,273
you said you wanted to live like Grandmother from now on.

68
00:05:39,272 --> 00:05:43,973
You knew everything about her, but you still said that to me.

69
00:05:47,082 --> 00:05:48,882
What did you mean by that?

70
00:05:48,882 --> 00:05:51,482
Are you going to kill me or something?

71
00:05:52,352 --> 00:05:54,622
There's no reason I couldn't.

72
00:06:07,002 --> 00:06:08,903
If you

73
00:06:10,473 --> 00:06:15,303
get in the way of that baby becoming the owner of Soonyang, that is.

74
00:06:16,543 --> 00:06:18,943
I don't care who it is.

75
00:06:18,943 --> 00:06:21,242
I can do anything.

76
00:06:22,812 --> 00:06:25,012
Just like your grandmother.

77
00:06:30,923 --> 00:06:33,123
So you'd better get your act together.

78
00:06:33,863 --> 00:06:35,762
It starts with you.

79
00:07:07,062 --> 00:07:09,063
Are you anxious?

80
00:07:10,632 --> 00:07:13,562
Since we're going all in,

81
00:07:14,632 --> 00:07:18,033
one ace card won't do.

82
00:07:21,243 --> 00:07:22,843
Then what?

83
00:07:24,613 --> 00:07:26,542
Don't worry.

84
00:07:27,343 --> 00:07:30,483
I'm holding the joker in this round.

85
00:07:36,623 --> 00:07:39,863
   

86
00:07:39,863 --> 00:07:41,823
   

87
00:07:41,823 --> 00:07:42,993
   

88
00:07:42,993 --> 00:07:48,062
Next, we'll discuss the appointment of the CEO of Soonyang Financial Holding Company.

89
00:07:48,062 --> 00:07:53,373
The board of directors recommended Director Lee Hang Jae.

90
00:07:53,373 --> 00:07:56,192
   

91
00:07:59,512 --> 00:08:02,383
Board member Jin Do Jun is another candidate.

92
00:08:10,252 --> 00:08:14,393
All right. We'll vote to decide.

93
00:08:14,393 --> 00:08:16,063
Is everyone ready?

94
00:08:19,562 --> 00:08:22,263
He used violence against Chairman Jin in the hospital room?

95
00:08:22,263 --> 00:08:25,613
Was it the shock that killed him? 
    

96
00:08:28,442 --> 00:08:30,843
This certainly disqualifies Jin Do Jun for the position.

97
00:08:30,843 --> 00:08:33,542
Are these texts really true?

98
00:08:33,542 --> 00:08:35,143
We demand an explanation.

99
00:08:35,143 --> 00:08:38,283
- Explain this. 
 - Everyone, let's not vote.

100
00:08:41,753 --> 00:08:44,722
To bring order back to this room so that we can proceed,

101
00:08:44,722 --> 00:08:47,822
I hereby exercise my authority as the chairperson

102
00:08:47,822 --> 00:08:51,332
and ask Director Jin Do Jun to provide an explanation.

103
00:08:52,063 --> 00:08:55,502
Is the content of the text message true?

104
00:08:57,772 --> 00:08:59,533
It is not true.

105
00:08:59,533 --> 00:09:02,172
We don't believe him. Can he prove it with evidence?

106
00:09:02,172 --> 00:09:04,343
How are we supposed to believe him?

107
00:09:04,343 --> 00:09:06,112
Quiet down, please.

108
00:09:09,483 --> 00:09:11,482
Can you prove it?

109
00:09:20,262 --> 00:09:21,492
Yes.

110
00:09:21,492 --> 00:09:23,932
   

111
00:09:23,932 --> 00:09:25,393
Yes.

112
00:09:25,393 --> 00:09:29,862
There is one way Director Jin Do Jun can clear his name.

113
00:09:29,862 --> 00:09:32,172
In the late chairman's room at the hospital,

114
00:09:32,172 --> 00:09:35,003
there was a camera recording everything,

115
00:09:35,003 --> 00:09:38,343
which the hospital staff use to monitor their VIP patients.

116
00:09:38,343 --> 00:09:42,683
Why don't we check the footage here?

117
00:09:42,683 --> 00:09:44,753
Good idea. Let's do that.

118
00:09:44,753 --> 00:09:46,703
Find the footage now.

119
00:09:48,953 --> 00:09:51,253
Please quiet down.

120
00:09:51,253 --> 00:09:53,153
Do you agree to this?

121
00:09:55,823 --> 00:09:57,663
Board member Jin Do Jun.

122
00:10:03,373 --> 00:10:07,402
That will be impossible.

123
00:10:08,473 --> 00:10:11,343
"Impossible?" What do you mean?

124
00:10:12,313 --> 00:10:15,542
The footage is gone.

125
00:10:17,753 --> 00:10:22,123
The board member Jin Do Jun here ordered me personally to get rid of it.

126
00:10:25,092 --> 00:10:28,542
 Then I can do what I want with it with my authority, right? 

127
00:10:28,542 --> 00:10:30,923
 Please delete the footage. 

128
00:10:45,412 --> 00:10:48,743
If nothing bad had happened in the room that day,

129
00:10:48,743 --> 00:10:53,213
why would he have asked me to delete the footage?

130
00:10:59,152 --> 00:11:00,992
Please be quiet.

131
00:11:00,992 --> 00:11:02,792
It is not true.

132
00:11:02,792 --> 00:11:05,292
Please let me speak, Chairperson.

133
00:11:07,702 --> 00:11:10,973
All right, please quiet down. Let me clear this up.

134
00:11:10,973 --> 00:11:15,002
This is not a courtroom to prove innocence.

135
00:11:15,002 --> 00:11:17,942
However, the leader's sense or lack of morality

136
00:11:17,942 --> 00:11:21,512
could make or break the future of the company.

137
00:11:21,512 --> 00:11:25,082
The late chairman wished to choose a leader

138
00:11:25,082 --> 00:11:28,353
who could lead the right way.

139
00:11:28,353 --> 00:11:30,453
Take your time to think about who would be

140
00:11:30,453 --> 00:11:33,443
the best person for the role before you vote.

141
00:11:34,162 --> 00:11:36,023
All right, then.

142
00:11:36,023 --> 00:11:39,263
Let's begin.

143
00:11:39,263 --> 00:11:41,762
 Mr. Chairman is 

144
00:11:43,302 --> 00:11:46,902
 experiencing symptoms of delirium at the moment. 

145
00:11:52,713 --> 00:11:54,713
 So? 

146
00:11:54,713 --> 00:11:57,852
 Have you decided to join hands with me? 

147
00:12:00,753 --> 00:12:06,193
 I am now too old and tired to keep on working as a mere farmer. 

148
00:12:12,292 --> 00:12:15,332
 Please give me some shares. 

149
00:12:16,032 --> 00:12:18,172
 I helped Soonyang grow to what it is today. 

150
00:12:18,172 --> 00:12:22,422
 I wish to own a plot of land in the company, no matter how small it is. 

151
00:12:35,422 --> 00:12:39,123
 That painting has surely found its place. 

152
00:12:43,462 --> 00:12:46,593
 I suppose you liked my gift. 

153
00:12:56,143 --> 00:13:00,412
I will now announce the results. Director Lee Hang Jae

154
00:13:00,412 --> 00:13:03,533
has been appointed CEO of Soonyang Financial Holding Company.

155
00:13:05,683 --> 00:13:08,633
   

156
00:13:12,723 --> 00:13:14,023
   

157
00:13:26,402 --> 00:13:29,202
Do Jun, have you thought about this?

158
00:13:30,672 --> 00:13:34,122
Would Chairman Jin Yang Cheol have told me

159
00:13:34,122 --> 00:13:37,283
to delete the security footage?

160
00:13:48,493 --> 00:13:52,263
So after all,

161
00:13:52,263 --> 00:13:55,203
we're the owners of Soonyang Financial Holding Company.

162
00:13:57,332 --> 00:13:59,332
Congratulations.

163
00:14:00,172 --> 00:14:02,473
We jointly own thirty percent of the shares.

164
00:14:02,473 --> 00:14:06,072
Add the CEO's friendly stakes, then we're at 37 percent.

165
00:14:06,072 --> 00:14:09,542
Do Jun is no match for us now.

166
00:14:09,542 --> 00:14:11,752
We used Mr. Lee

167
00:14:11,752 --> 00:14:13,922
and labeled Do Jun as an immoral child

168
00:14:13,922 --> 00:14:17,322
in front of all the shareholders,

169
00:14:17,322 --> 00:14:19,593
so he'll have to lie low for the time being.

170
00:14:19,593 --> 00:14:25,892
We now have voting rights in all the subsidiaries under the holding company.

171
00:14:25,892 --> 00:14:29,802
My, this is nice. The holding company!

172
00:14:29,802 --> 00:14:33,972
Right, as long as one of us doesn't betray the other.

173
00:14:34,603 --> 00:14:39,142
Hyung Young Ki, no one has our backs now.

174
00:14:39,142 --> 00:14:43,312
We only have each other under the sky.

175
00:14:46,052 --> 00:14:47,752
Right?

176
00:15:02,333 --> 00:15:04,572
Congratulations.

177
00:15:05,473 --> 00:15:07,503
Thank you.

178
00:15:09,102 --> 00:15:11,973
About the shares we discussed the other day...

179
00:15:11,973 --> 00:15:14,173
- Right. 
 - Yes.

180
00:15:22,022 --> 00:15:24,422
   

181
00:15:25,552 --> 00:15:27,893
My grandfather thought it was just a borrowed-name account

182
00:15:27,893 --> 00:15:31,292
in your name.

183
00:15:31,292 --> 00:15:35,462
But I suppose you thought the account was yours.

184
00:15:36,932 --> 00:15:41,332
I understand you get crumbs on your hands when handling bread.

185
00:15:41,332 --> 00:15:44,992
Just resign. I'll consider it your severance package.

186
00:15:46,743 --> 00:15:50,193
Or would you rather be on the news as an embezzler?

187
00:15:57,893 --> 00:16:02,463
Was this your plan from the start, from the moment

188
00:16:02,463 --> 00:16:05,463
you offered me the CEO position?

189
00:16:05,463 --> 00:16:08,413
Did you just need a knife to get rid of Do Jun?

190
00:16:09,202 --> 00:16:13,103
The family fighting during Grandfather's funeral wouldn't be a pretty sight.

191
00:16:20,513 --> 00:16:22,982
   

192
00:16:28,953 --> 00:16:31,523
My whole life, I was completely dedicated to Soonyang.

193
00:16:31,523 --> 00:16:35,292
I joined the company way before you were even born.

194
00:16:35,292 --> 00:16:38,833
Your grandfather and I grew Soonyang into what it is today.

195
00:16:38,833 --> 00:16:40,833
So why...

196
00:16:40,833 --> 00:16:44,533
Why should I be treated like this? Just why?

197
00:16:47,673 --> 00:16:49,943
I apologize.

198
00:16:49,943 --> 00:16:52,642
I guess you feel deeply wronged.

199
00:16:53,913 --> 00:16:57,363
Are you that desperate to be treated like an owner?

200
00:17:10,832 --> 00:17:13,593
Then you should be born again.

201
00:17:37,153 --> 00:17:39,023
   

202
00:17:56,243 --> 00:17:59,243
Grandfather truly is an interesting man.

203
00:18:00,513 --> 00:18:03,812
He said he wanted you to be the CEO of the holding company.

204
00:18:03,812 --> 00:18:06,752
So what's with the will then?

205
00:18:07,452 --> 00:18:09,952
I thought long and hard.

206
00:18:09,952 --> 00:18:14,553
If he was just joking, that's mean. And if it's a prank, that's cruel.

207
00:18:14,553 --> 00:18:16,693
After long, careful consideration,

208
00:18:16,693 --> 00:18:19,332
I decided to step in as his eldest grandson.

209
00:18:19,332 --> 00:18:21,602
I wanted to show you clearly in front of the shareholders

210
00:18:21,602 --> 00:18:25,203
how Grandfather's will should be interpreted.

211
00:18:26,802 --> 00:18:29,603
Now, you're no match for us in this war.

212
00:18:29,603 --> 00:18:33,573
You cannot exercise any management or voting rights.

213
00:18:33,573 --> 00:18:37,842
Most importantly, you can no longer say

214
00:18:38,913 --> 00:18:42,313
that you're Chairman Jin Yang Cheol's favorite grandson.

215
00:18:44,092 --> 00:18:48,023
There is only one thing you can do against Soonyang now.

216
00:18:48,023 --> 00:18:50,892
Hand over all your shares in the holding company to me.

217
00:18:50,892 --> 00:18:53,293
I'll pay a handsome price.

218
00:18:58,973 --> 00:19:02,473
Grandfather wrote in his will that you should

219
00:19:02,473 --> 00:19:05,692
live a life that has nothing to do with Soonyang.

220
00:19:06,812 --> 00:19:09,212
How about you honor his last wishes?

221
00:19:09,212 --> 00:19:11,882
As a dutiful grandson should.

222
00:19:16,852 --> 00:19:19,392
You seem quite confident.

223
00:19:21,392 --> 00:19:24,992
I've been racking my brain but still can't figure out

224
00:19:24,992 --> 00:19:29,432
what Grandfather really meant by what he wrote in his will.

225
00:19:38,403 --> 00:19:40,543
This one thing I know.

226
00:19:42,743 --> 00:19:45,383
If Grandfather was in my situation now,

227
00:19:46,153 --> 00:19:48,803
I know what kind of choice he would make.

228
00:19:57,393 --> 00:20:00,663
My dear fellow members of the National Assembly. 
    

229
00:20:00,663 --> 00:20:02,903
Vote against the bill to ease the Separation

230
00:20:02,903 --> 00:20:04,073
of Banking and Commerce Act.

231
00:20:04,073 --> 00:20:05,532
   

232
00:20:05,532 --> 00:20:08,243
Put a stop to Soonyang's plan to establish

233
00:20:08,243 --> 00:20:10,743
a financial holding company.

234
00:20:10,743 --> 00:20:12,642
This bill was devised to justify

235
00:20:12,642 --> 00:20:17,583
Soonyang's succession plans that seek to avoid the legal responsibilities that come with it.

236
00:20:17,583 --> 00:20:20,182
The conglomerates are trying to push the bill through

237
00:20:20,182 --> 00:20:23,753
in order to avoid the astronomical inheritance taxes.

238
00:20:23,753 --> 00:20:26,953
We need systems and rules in place

239
00:20:26,953 --> 00:20:29,163
to keep the conglomerates in check

240
00:20:29,163 --> 00:20:31,063
in order to alleviate economic polarization

241
00:20:31,063 --> 00:20:35,593
so that we can build a world where the economically weak can coexist with them.

242
00:20:35,593 --> 00:20:38,183
   

243
00:20:38,183 --> 00:20:40,433
I, Choi Chang Je,

244
00:20:40,433 --> 00:20:42,503
promise you that I will open the threshold

245
00:20:42,503 --> 00:20:44,942
through economic democratization!

246
00:20:44,942 --> 00:20:47,813
 Earlier today, Mayor Choi Chang Je held a press conference, 

247
00:20:47,813 --> 00:20:49,742
 where he stated he was against the bill 

248
00:20:49,742 --> 00:20:50,852
 to mitigate the Financial and Industrial Separation Act, 

249
00:20:50,852 --> 00:20:52,182
 as it'd create legal loopholes for Soonyang 

250
00:20:52,182 --> 00:20:53,982
 prior to announcing he was running for President. 

251
00:20:53,982 --> 00:20:57,152
 He stated that the late chairman, Jin Yang Cheol, 

252
00:20:57,152 --> 00:20:59,990
 pushed for the establishment of the financial holding company 
   

253
00:20:59,990 --> 00:21:02,363
 to avoid having to pay astronomical inheritance taxes. 

254
00:21:02,363 --> 00:21:04,293
 Some suspect that the company might have taken 

255
00:21:04,293 --> 00:21:07,232
 expedient measures to establish its financial holding company. 

256
00:21:07,232 --> 00:21:08,932
 There are growing suspicions surrounding 

257
00:21:08,932 --> 00:21:10,573
 potential corrupt practices within Soonyang. 

258
00:21:10,573 --> 00:21:12,132
 The National Assembly has voted against the bill 

259
00:21:12,132 --> 00:21:14,343
 to mitigate the Financial and Industrial Separation Act, 

260
00:21:14,343 --> 00:21:16,543
 so the establishment of Soonyang Financial Holding Company 

261
00:21:16,543 --> 00:21:19,242
 is nullified. 

262
00:21:19,812 --> 00:21:22,213
If our plans for the holding company fall through,

263
00:21:22,213 --> 00:21:24,212
what should we take care of first?

264
00:21:24,212 --> 00:21:26,553
We could've avoided at least a trillion won  ($1B) 

265
00:21:26,553 --> 00:21:28,652
in inheritance taxes by using the shares.

266
00:21:28,652 --> 00:21:30,123
As soon as the market opens tomorrow,

267
00:21:30,123 --> 00:21:32,453
all the stocks connected to the holding company will plummet.

268
00:21:32,453 --> 00:21:34,993
Soonyang Insurance will probably drop to below 70k won  ($70) per share. 

269
00:21:34,993 --> 00:21:37,733
The moment they vote against the bill,

270
00:21:37,733 --> 00:21:40,193
we'll lose four trillion won  ($4B) in cash. 

271
00:21:40,193 --> 00:21:43,203
Darn it! They say you should never trust your brother-in-law.

272
00:21:43,203 --> 00:21:47,732
Why is Chang Je suddenly out to get us?

273
00:21:50,572 --> 00:21:54,313
Shouldn't you know him better by now?

274
00:21:54,313 --> 00:21:55,913
Do you really think

275
00:21:55,913 --> 00:21:58,913
that Chang Je came up with this plan?

276
00:21:58,913 --> 00:22:00,853
Do you all think that?

277
00:22:02,753 --> 00:22:04,823
   

278
00:22:04,823 --> 00:22:07,222
Hey, Nephew. People now call me

279
00:22:07,222 --> 00:22:10,192
the icon of economic democratization.

280
00:22:10,192 --> 00:22:12,263
They say, with just a few words, I managed to persuade them

281
00:22:12,263 --> 00:22:15,902
to vote against the bill that was about to pass easily.

282
00:22:15,902 --> 00:22:18,872
 Anyway, how did you come up with an idea like this? 

283
00:22:18,872 --> 00:22:23,203
 So you used people's anger toward Chairman Jin Yang Cheol 

284
00:22:23,203 --> 00:22:25,212
 as an impetus 

285
00:22:25,212 --> 00:22:27,872
 to unite public opinion. 

286
00:22:27,872 --> 00:22:30,943
People do like heroes,

287
00:22:30,943 --> 00:22:33,282
but they get a real kick out of watching a hero fall.

288
00:22:33,282 --> 00:22:34,822
That's right.

289
00:22:34,822 --> 00:22:36,782
But no one would ever imagine

290
00:22:36,782 --> 00:22:39,193
that the person who made the hero fall

291
00:22:39,193 --> 00:22:44,033
was none other than his favorite grandson.

292
00:22:44,033 --> 00:22:45,793
Right?

293
00:22:45,793 --> 00:22:48,203
 Oh, the party leader is here. 

294
00:22:48,203 --> 00:22:50,053
 I'll talk to you later. 

295
00:23:02,083 --> 00:23:06,083
 Next news. The news that Soonyang Financial Holding Company, 

296
00:23:06,083 --> 00:23:07,623
 Chairman Jin Yang Cheol's long-cherished ambition, 

297
00:23:07,623 --> 00:23:11,253
 was actually a part of the company's plan to avoid inheritance taxes 

298
00:23:11,253 --> 00:23:16,623
 is quickly making the countless mourners across the country turn away. 

299
00:23:16,623 --> 00:23:19,763
 No one can deny that the late chairman, Jin Yang Cheol, 

300
00:23:19,763 --> 00:23:21,663
 was a successful business leader. 

301
00:23:21,663 --> 00:23:23,973
 However, we also cannot deny that he tried 

302
00:23:23,973 --> 00:23:26,203
 to influence politicians until his final moments 

303
00:23:26,203 --> 00:23:31,942
 to illegally transfer his assets and take expedient measures to avoid inheritance taxes. 

304
00:23:31,942 --> 00:23:35,912
   

305
00:23:42,422 --> 00:23:43,823
   

306
00:23:48,593 --> 00:23:50,992
   

307
00:24:07,142 --> 00:24:11,812
 Lawyer Park, I want to change my will. 

308
00:24:11,812 --> 00:24:14,082
 It's all because of that rascal, Do Jun. 

309
00:24:15,283 --> 00:24:18,923
 He's no good! 

310
00:24:18,923 --> 00:24:22,763
 That rascal. I can't stand him. 

311
00:24:22,763 --> 00:24:26,463
 That's why I want to change my will. 

312
00:24:26,463 --> 00:24:29,363
 Why are you so unsatisfied with Do Jun, Mr. Chairman? 

313
00:24:29,363 --> 00:24:31,572
 Do you know why that punk 

314
00:24:31,572 --> 00:24:35,072
 is trying so hard to save Soonyang Motors with all his might? 

315
00:24:35,072 --> 00:24:39,312
 He knows his grandfather is dying, so he feels sorry for me. 

316
00:24:40,112 --> 00:24:43,112
 That's why he's peeing on his frozen foot. 

317
00:24:44,812 --> 00:24:46,482
 That little brat. 

318
00:24:48,982 --> 00:24:50,483
 Don't try to change my mind. 

319
00:24:50,483 --> 00:24:54,022
 That punk is not getting a single penny from me. 

320
00:24:54,022 --> 00:24:56,992
 Sir, Do Jun cares for you as your grandson... 

321
00:24:56,992 --> 00:24:58,732
 You fool! 

322
00:24:59,363 --> 00:25:01,203
 It's not like bullets avoid family members 

323
00:25:01,203 --> 00:25:05,103
 when you're fighting a war! 

324
00:25:05,103 --> 00:25:08,842
 One thing that a fighter has no use for, like his appendix, 

325
00:25:08,842 --> 00:25:11,413
 is compassion. Sympathy! 

326
00:25:11,413 --> 00:25:16,083
 You cannot afford to drag such useless emotions to a war. 

327
00:25:16,083 --> 00:25:18,383
 It'll only weigh you down. 

328
00:25:19,913 --> 00:25:24,093
 But if you leave nothing for Do Jun as this will states, 

329
00:25:24,093 --> 00:25:26,053
 the succession plans will face obstacles, Sir. 

330
00:25:26,053 --> 00:25:28,503
 I will push him to the edge of a cliff. 

331
00:25:29,863 --> 00:25:31,692
 That brat... 

332
00:25:31,692 --> 00:25:35,033
 He'll do anything to survive. 

333
00:25:36,333 --> 00:25:40,302
 I want him to see how he can be when he's hit rock bottom. 

334
00:25:43,243 --> 00:25:45,273
 I know that 

335
00:25:45,273 --> 00:25:47,272
 he is someone 

336
00:25:47,272 --> 00:25:49,713
 who wouldn't hesitate to sell me 

337
00:25:49,713 --> 00:25:52,453
 to buy Soonyang. 

338
00:25:53,513 --> 00:25:55,723
 If he tramples all over me to go forward, 

339
00:25:55,723 --> 00:26:00,222
 there will be nothing he can't do in the future. 

340
00:26:05,062 --> 00:26:07,292
 Only then... 

341
00:26:09,403 --> 00:26:12,402
 can that rascal protect Soonyang and survive. 

342
00:26:16,203 --> 00:26:18,972
 Sir, it's ready. 

343
00:26:18,972 --> 00:26:22,413
 This video can serve as your legal will. 

344
00:26:22,413 --> 00:26:25,713
 - Okay. 
 - Shall we begin then? 

345
00:26:34,993 --> 00:26:36,823
 Sir. 

346
00:26:38,333 --> 00:26:43,632
 Just relax and say what you'd like to tell Do Jun. 

347
00:26:48,472 --> 00:26:50,402
 Do Jun? 

348
00:26:52,142 --> 00:26:55,013
 Who is... 

349
00:26:55,013 --> 00:26:57,642
 Do Jun, Chairman Jin? 

350
00:27:17,532 --> 00:27:19,803
 Do Jun? 

351
00:27:35,782 --> 00:27:38,653
 He's my grandson. 

352
00:27:43,963 --> 00:27:48,193
 The one who takes after me the most. 

353
00:27:52,102 --> 00:27:54,573
 My grandson. 

354
00:28:46,953 --> 00:28:52,923
 It's Chairman Jin's inheritance he left for you, Do Jun. 

355
00:29:16,953 --> 00:29:18,792
It's this one.

356
00:29:28,132 --> 00:29:29,763
   

357
00:29:43,913 --> 00:29:47,552
 Chairman Jin made sure I handed it over to you 

358
00:29:47,552 --> 00:29:50,812
 once you understood the meaning of his will. 

359
00:30:08,873 --> 00:30:10,572
Soonyang Micro.

360
00:30:10,572 --> 00:30:14,013
 There was a document that wasn't on the list. 

361
00:30:15,342 --> 00:30:18,053
 It was an old document that had passed the preservation year. 

362
00:30:18,053 --> 00:30:19,682
 So at first, I thought of discarding it. 

363
00:30:19,682 --> 00:30:22,882
 But there was a record that a fairly large amount of money 

364
00:30:22,882 --> 00:30:25,923
 had been stored for a long time. 

365
00:30:32,480 --> 00:30:35,560
   

366
00:30:36,903 --> 00:30:42,003
 Soonyang Micro is a dummy company that only exists on paper. 

367
00:30:42,003 --> 00:30:48,112
 Someone is siphoning Soonyang's money overseas through this paper company, Sir. 

368
00:30:48,112 --> 00:30:51,353
 Go retrieve Soonyang's assets that have been siphoned off overseas. 

369
00:30:51,353 --> 00:30:55,523
 That is your first mission as the senior finance manager. 

370
00:30:56,590 --> 00:30:59,070
   

371
00:31:08,033 --> 00:31:10,032
Are you sure?

372
00:31:10,032 --> 00:31:14,503
Is this truly the legacy Grandfather had left for me?

373
00:31:14,503 --> 00:31:18,013
Chairman Jin had worked hard preparing it for quite a long time.

374
00:31:18,013 --> 00:31:21,172
To give it to the successor over Soonyang.

375
00:31:21,172 --> 00:31:24,613
Now, no one in Soonyang is aware

376
00:31:24,613 --> 00:31:27,252
of that money's existence.

377
00:31:27,252 --> 00:31:30,322
And, of course, the money can't be tracked.

378
00:31:30,322 --> 00:31:34,692
It's a perfect slush fund that can't be reduced by gift or inheritance tax.

379
00:31:34,692 --> 00:31:36,773
Chairman Jin had made sure

380
00:31:37,623 --> 00:31:40,392
I understood multiple times.

381
00:31:40,392 --> 00:31:45,662
To hand you that only when you have attained the lesson

382
00:31:46,573 --> 00:31:48,833
behind his will.

383
00:31:48,833 --> 00:31:51,242
But why did he leave it to me?

384
00:31:53,473 --> 00:31:55,582
If it were such a perfect slush fund,

385
00:31:55,582 --> 00:31:59,782
nobody would have found it if you had kept it, Mr. Lee.

386
00:32:00,683 --> 00:32:04,182
Was it your last loyalty to Grandfather

387
00:32:04,182 --> 00:32:06,303
or something like that?

388
00:32:12,192 --> 00:32:15,203
If, at this point, I were to tell you that was the case

389
00:32:15,203 --> 00:32:17,263
would you believe me?

390
00:32:20,032 --> 00:32:23,603
Being born a servant was not my choice.

391
00:32:24,773 --> 00:32:28,542
But I could choose the owner to serve.

392
00:32:32,753 --> 00:32:35,853
Vice-Chairman Jin Young Ki or Jin Dong Ki.

393
00:32:36,652 --> 00:32:39,302
I can't hand over Soonyang to them.

394
00:32:41,593 --> 00:32:44,493
Aren't we on the same page, Do Jun?

395
00:32:47,093 --> 00:32:52,333
 He has been elected as the 16th presidential candidate of our party. 

396
00:32:56,942 --> 00:33:00,313
 - Lee Chang Min! 
 - For President! 

397
00:33:01,283 --> 00:33:02,743
Are you happy?

398
00:33:02,743 --> 00:33:06,653
Mayor Choi Chang Je, the icon of economic democratization!

399
00:33:07,282 --> 00:33:11,222
I only found out today that Korea still had a sense of justice.

400
00:33:11,222 --> 00:33:15,252
I glamorized and made you, a self-supporting student from the countryside, the mayor of Seoul.

401
00:33:15,252 --> 00:33:17,832
And you betray your wife's family?

402
00:33:17,832 --> 00:33:21,293
Such a man shouldn't become the president.

403
00:33:23,803 --> 00:33:27,503
That shrewd Do Jun didn't like what he had.

404
00:33:27,503 --> 00:33:29,803
So he gathered everyone and turned everything over.

405
00:33:29,803 --> 00:33:31,713
He egged you on

406
00:33:31,713 --> 00:33:33,542
to bring the holding company to naught

407
00:33:33,542 --> 00:33:36,742
and repeal the separation of industrial and financial capital.

408
00:33:38,012 --> 00:33:39,912
No. It was me.

409
00:33:39,912 --> 00:33:43,683
Bringing the financial holding company to naught was my idea from beginning to end.

410
00:33:43,683 --> 00:33:46,153
A tycoon should never own a bank.

411
00:33:46,153 --> 00:33:49,893
That's the political conviction of Choi Chang Je, the tycoon sharpshooter.

412
00:33:52,332 --> 00:33:54,362
Let's hear about your political conviction.

413
00:33:54,362 --> 00:33:57,903
So who will become the president?

414
00:33:57,903 --> 00:34:00,872
For goodness' sake.

415
00:34:00,872 --> 00:34:03,842
You're really something. You really are.

416
00:34:03,842 --> 00:34:06,542
Is that something to ask me right at this moment?

417
00:34:06,542 --> 00:34:09,912
Yes. Right at this moment,

418
00:34:09,912 --> 00:34:13,083
I must tell my brothers, who might end up paying over one trillion won  (1$B) 

419
00:34:13,083 --> 00:34:15,352
as inheritance tax because of you,

420
00:34:15,352 --> 00:34:19,523
that I, Jin Hwa Young, am still a useful card

421
00:34:19,523 --> 00:34:22,122
so that your second political life can begin.

422
00:34:22,122 --> 00:34:23,793
Stop it.

423
00:34:23,793 --> 00:34:27,213
So tell me. Who will win the presidential election?

424
00:34:27,213 --> 00:34:29,783
Who must we deliver the money to?

425
00:34:34,072 --> 00:34:35,703
The one in favor

426
00:34:38,213 --> 00:34:40,163
has already been decided, no?

427
00:34:41,713 --> 00:34:43,313
Who's the one in favor? Tell me.

428
00:34:43,313 --> 00:34:44,812
This is the men's room!

429
00:34:44,812 --> 00:34:46,583
Who is it?

430
00:34:48,523 --> 00:34:50,182
Are you sure he's in favor?

431
00:34:50,182 --> 00:34:53,553
The ruling party candidate is causing a squall right now.

432
00:34:53,553 --> 00:34:55,992
Come on. It's just a tempest inside a teacup.

433
00:34:55,992 --> 00:34:59,722
Who can go up against us by catching a mere piggy bank?

434
00:34:59,722 --> 00:35:05,102
Daeyoung Group also sent off two dump trunks of bills a couple of days ago.

435
00:35:05,102 --> 00:35:07,203
This country is still a long way off.

436
00:35:07,203 --> 00:35:08,903
That candidate in favor.

437
00:35:08,903 --> 00:35:10,742
Isn't he known to be upright?

438
00:35:10,742 --> 00:35:15,372
The more reason he'll love money that's new and crisp.

439
00:35:16,843 --> 00:35:20,612
Let's go with the candidate in favor before it's too late.

440
00:35:20,612 --> 00:35:22,632
Do we not need insurance

441
00:35:23,782 --> 00:35:25,492
for the other candidate?

442
00:35:25,492 --> 00:35:27,722
Let's give them a small token of our sincerity.

443
00:35:27,722 --> 00:35:31,992
If Grandfather had been alive, he would've fully supported one candidate.

444
00:35:33,392 --> 00:35:35,803
Hyungnim Young Ki,

445
00:35:35,803 --> 00:35:38,963
we're in the same boat now, okay?

446
00:35:44,443 --> 00:35:47,073
There won't be a need to turn back.

447
00:35:47,073 --> 00:35:51,013
You, my brother, and I agree, after all.

448
00:35:53,113 --> 00:35:57,082
Gosh, really. Our father must feel so reassured,

449
00:35:57,082 --> 00:36:01,592
seeing the close bond the three of his children have.

450
00:36:01,592 --> 00:36:03,622
Geez, Hwa Young.

451
00:36:09,063 --> 00:36:13,533
I thought the media would die down once Uncle lost the candidate election.

452
00:36:13,533 --> 00:36:15,972
But he's still at the center of the attention.

453
00:36:15,972 --> 00:36:18,972
A chaebol should not own a bank.

454
00:36:18,972 --> 00:36:21,042
Forty-one percent of the general public agrees.

455
00:36:21,042 --> 00:36:23,383
Seventy-one percent of economics professors agree.

456
00:36:23,383 --> 00:36:26,353
I'm going to make a constitutional appeal.

457
00:36:26,353 --> 00:36:28,182
I will, period.

458
00:36:28,182 --> 00:36:31,853
How come? Isn't it a chance for us?

459
00:36:31,853 --> 00:36:34,122
The holding company establishment went to pieces.

460
00:36:34,122 --> 00:36:39,062
Joint shares and voting rights with Uncle Young Ki will mean nothing.

461
00:36:39,062 --> 00:36:41,283
We need to find a way to survive.

462
00:36:41,963 --> 00:36:46,102
So what? Do you have one in mind?

463
00:36:46,133 --> 00:36:48,232
Don't worry, Father.

464
00:36:48,972 --> 00:36:53,112
Right now, there's only one way to become Soonyang Group's head.

465
00:36:53,112 --> 00:36:55,983
It's to have the most shares of Soonyang affiliates

466
00:36:55,983 --> 00:36:58,512
and become the largest shareholder of Soonyang Corporation.

467
00:36:58,512 --> 00:37:01,283
Uncle Dong Ki doesn't even come close to your Soonyang Corporation shares.

468
00:37:01,283 --> 00:37:03,553
Your uncle isn't someone

469
00:37:03,553 --> 00:37:07,822
who will easily give up the head position to me.

470
00:37:09,662 --> 00:37:14,093
By now, I bet he's figuring out the numbers like crazy.

471
00:37:14,733 --> 00:37:17,063
Say that again. Do what?

472
00:37:17,063 --> 00:37:22,932
Let's separate financial affiliates from Soonyang Group and make them independent.

473
00:37:24,503 --> 00:37:27,213
We can use public opinion as the pretext.

474
00:37:27,213 --> 00:37:29,613
Rather than the hopeless Soonyang Group head,

475
00:37:29,613 --> 00:37:32,613
doesn't the chairman of a financial group

476
00:37:32,613 --> 00:37:34,553
sound good?

477
00:37:36,523 --> 00:37:39,893
Gosh. Well, I...

478
00:37:41,392 --> 00:37:45,123
For Soonyang to become a national company,

479
00:37:45,963 --> 00:37:48,363
I'll sacrifice myself.

480
00:37:53,273 --> 00:37:56,142
What brings you here so early, CEO Oh?

481
00:37:56,142 --> 00:37:58,373
Is something going on?

482
00:37:58,373 --> 00:38:01,512
Your face is telling me you haven't heard of the news.

483
00:38:01,512 --> 00:38:03,112
What news?

484
00:38:03,112 --> 00:38:08,552
The board of directors of Soonyang Investment dismissed me from the CEO position.

485
00:38:11,452 --> 00:38:13,392
It's not only Soonyang Investment.

486
00:38:13,392 --> 00:38:16,162
It includes Soonyang Fire Insurance and Soonyang Asset Management.

487
00:38:16,162 --> 00:38:18,533
The board of directors rose up and replaced all the CEOs.

488
00:38:18,533 --> 00:38:19,662
I know.

489
00:38:19,662 --> 00:38:22,033
Both the board of directors of Soonyang Investment and Soonyang Fire Insurance

490
00:38:22,033 --> 00:38:23,932
are former CEOs or the owners' families.

491
00:38:23,932 --> 00:38:26,432
They're under Vice-Chairman Jin Dong Ki's influence.

492
00:38:26,432 --> 00:38:27,872
Yes.

493
00:38:28,572 --> 00:38:32,722
That means Vice-Chairman Jin Dong Ki has started to move independently.

494
00:38:34,443 --> 00:38:36,782
Oh, let me get you some coffee. Please wait.

495
00:38:36,782 --> 00:38:39,382
 Everyone! 

496
00:38:39,382 --> 00:38:42,953
 Please become wealthy! 

497
00:38:42,953 --> 00:38:45,322
 Promise! 

498
00:38:45,322 --> 00:38:48,823
 Daeyoung thinks about your success. 

499
00:38:48,823 --> 00:38:50,192
 Daeyoung Card. 

500
00:38:50,192 --> 00:38:54,362
CEO Oh. It's time we sell it.

501
00:38:54,362 --> 00:38:56,163
Soonyang Card.

502
00:38:58,933 --> 00:39:01,472
   

503
00:39:02,943 --> 00:39:04,993
 You're being transferred, Prosecutor Seo. 

504
00:39:06,273 --> 00:39:09,812
 Maybe you bit too hard into Soonyang until now. 

505
00:39:11,042 --> 00:39:13,753
   

506
00:39:13,753 --> 00:39:18,183
Thanks to you, I get to work at the Supreme Central Investigation Division.

507
00:39:18,183 --> 00:39:20,192
Are you that pleased?

508
00:39:21,123 --> 00:39:25,362
I'm glad. I was worried I might have imposed on you.

509
00:39:25,362 --> 00:39:28,533
You weren't too happy about it, were you?

510
00:39:28,533 --> 00:39:30,063
But it's a promotion.

511
00:39:30,063 --> 00:39:31,933
Is it?

512
00:39:31,933 --> 00:39:33,532
I thought it was a demotion.

513
00:39:33,532 --> 00:39:35,142
A demotion? No way.

514
00:39:35,142 --> 00:39:39,803
This is the Prosecutor's Office's flower, Central Investigation Division. It has great power.

515
00:39:39,803 --> 00:39:42,613
We won't know until the presidential election is over.

516
00:39:42,613 --> 00:39:46,212
But I heard the next government would abolish the Central Investigation Division.

517
00:39:46,212 --> 00:39:49,852
That rumor has been going on since the civilian government.

518
00:39:49,852 --> 00:39:51,952
This time, it's not just a rumor.

519
00:39:51,952 --> 00:39:55,992
You see, I got transferred to this division.

520
00:39:56,722 --> 00:40:00,992
If the Central Investigation Division were going to keep thriving,

521
00:40:00,992 --> 00:40:03,732
I would not be here.

522
00:40:04,662 --> 00:40:08,472
I'm going home first. You should, too.

