723
00:53:32,272 --> 00:53:33,943
Good grief.

724
00:53:34,943 --> 00:53:38,643
What now? Go with the flow before it's too late?

725
00:53:38,643 --> 00:53:40,653
Two brothers should get on the same boat?

726
00:53:40,653 --> 00:53:43,122
How much money did I load on that boat?

727
00:53:43,122 --> 00:53:46,923
You should be helping me in some way as my older brother.

728
00:53:46,923 --> 00:53:49,292
What now? There's no need to turn back?

729
00:53:49,292 --> 00:53:51,093
We should unite as brothers?

730
00:53:51,093 --> 00:53:51,962
Okay, sure.

731
00:53:51,962 --> 00:53:56,293
Why don't you pray that we'll jump in the water together and die?

732
00:53:56,293 --> 00:53:59,332
You said the candidate in favor was decided.

733
00:53:59,972 --> 00:54:04,133
Didn't you say the law of an election is that the general trend cannot be overturned?

734
00:54:04,133 --> 00:54:06,512
I did. But don't you know?

735
00:54:06,512 --> 00:54:09,682
Everything comes with an exception. You Should've heard me out to the end.

736
00:54:09,682 --> 00:54:11,542
What did you say?

737
00:54:12,343 --> 00:54:15,513
The law of the Korean president elections is that the big trend cannot be overturned.

738
00:54:15,513 --> 00:54:18,723
However, that is only until a sharp gust blows.

739
00:54:18,723 --> 00:54:20,192
The opposition party had the general popularity,

